  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka Customs seizes Rs.16 mln worth illegal cigarettes; five arrested",
      "author": "Neshella Perera",
      "body_lines": [
        "ECONOMYNEXT \u2013 Sri Lanka Customs has seized 16 million rupees worth 810 cartons of cigarettes and arrested five individuals for attempting to smuggle the illegal consignment from Oman, it said in a statement..",
        "The five arrested had traveled to Sri Lanka through Oman Airlines via Dubai. The suspects are residents of Chilaw, Moratuwa and Maligawatta, Sri Lanka Customs said in a statement.",
        "The suspects were nabbed when they tried to use Green Channel, which is reserved for passengers who do not have to declare anything to the customs at the airport.. The suspects have failed to declare the cigarettes and pretended as they were their personal belongings, the Customs said.",
        "The cigarette stock contained 810 cartons of cigarettes and its market value is estimated to be around 16 million rupees.",
        "Airport Division of Sri Lanka Customs will impose fine on the confiscated cigarettes and will conduct further investigations. (Colombo/Aug 27/2022)"
      ],
